Resembled nothing in the world more than an 
underarm holster to carry the batteries. And we

07:12.369 --> 07:21.400
were at State Fair in 1939, my wife and I going 
around gawking, and a fella came up next to me He

07:22.578 --> 07:24.080
said, I'd like to see you for a minute. Well, he 
looked like he was big enough to.

07:31.548 --> 07:35.353
At least he impressed me, and I said, well, what 
about? He showed me his shield, and he said, let's

07:36.834 --> 07:40.639
step in here a minute. He said, will you kindly 
unbutton your shirt? He thought I was wearing a

07:43.762 --> 07:45.164
gun. Really? Under my left. A shoulder holster. 
Yeah. That's what it really, that's what it looked

07:52.548 --> 07:54.870
like. Well, with that hearing aid, I was quite 
relieved when I answered the telephone and I'd

07:56.251 --> 08:10.064
take the receiver and put it against the 
receiver's telephone against my receiver. I

08:10.084 --> 08:22.015
remember I was over at Livingston one night and I 
wanted to make a call and I took the receiver and put

08:10.084 --> 08:22.015
it against my hearing aid and started talking to 
the the transmitter. A little Mexican boy went

08:26.046 --> 08:30.732
nuts there trying to tell me, no, no, no, you don't 
use it that way. I finally opened my shirt and

08:33.036 --> 08:35.719
showed him. He said, oh. And I've had people come to 
my office and I had a piece of foam rubber in the top

08:40.166 --> 08:49.098
drawer of my desk. And when the telephones rang, it 
was one of them old fast ones that The receiver hung

08:53.264 --> 08:54.786
on the stand, you know. I'd take the receiver off 
and drop it in the desk so I could lean against it.

09:00.872 --> 09:04.817
And I'd just talk into the telephone. And the time a 
county agent came in, the little boy, oh, he was

09:04.837 --> 09:11.464
little, I'd say he was 10 or 11. Phone rang and I 
said, pardon me a minute. I took the receiver off

09:14.387 --> 09:19.693
and dropped it in the desk drawer and leaned 
against it and started talking. I had my hand free

09:19.713 --> 09:22.596
to use my pencil. The kid looked up and said, I'll be 
goddamned.

09:27.942 --> 09:30.485
So then I explained to him what I was doing. And I'd 
go out to examine the animal. I had an extra long

09:35.209 --> 09:36.690
cord on it. I'd take it off and put it against the 
animal and use it as a test scope. And it worked

09:40.914 --> 09:46.660
better than any I've ever had since.

09:46.680 --> 09:50.203
Well, 1943.

09:52.698 --> 09:57.545
Dr. Van Valkenburg died suddenly of a heart 
attack.

