Okay, now can we stop for a moment and talk about 
teaching and the curriculum back in the 1930s and

11:25.223 --> 11:29.988
the early 1940s. Was there an overall aim of the vet 
program at that time? Well, the overall aim then

11:37.876 --> 11:41.399
was primarily to turn out practitioners. Right. 
And they were, as I recall, six departments. There

11:48.766 --> 11:52.530
was bacteriology.

11:56.645 --> 12:01.850
Dr. Dunn,

11:56.645 --> 12:01.850
pathology doctor. What's that guy's name?

12:09.977 --> 12:15.782
Anyway, Dr. Jaggi was brought in in 1937 on public 
health. I was teaching parapsychology. Dr. Lent

12:19.285 --> 12:20.706
was teaching clinic.

12:23.369 --> 12:24.930
I can't think of the pathologist's name.

12:31.087 --> 12:33.209
I'll think of it after a while. Anyway, Dr. 
Marsteller was dean,

12:33.229 --> 12:43.821
and he also helped in the clinic.

12:47.845 --> 12:57.415
And since parasitology was only two, three-hour 
courses, I also helped in the clinic.

13:01.208 --> 13:03.511
In infected and non-infected diseases.

