What were the major, back in

20:32.834 --> 20:44.891
those days, what were the major problems in the 
field with the parasites? I mean, which were the

20:44.911 --> 20:48.877
major diseases that you were working to overcome? 
The parasites in cattle and horses primarily,

20:49.938 --> 20:58.150
since cattle were the mainstay of the Texas 
ranchers.

21:02.247 --> 21:06.072
and that includes knowledge of the drugs and the 
dosages. We did a lot of work on trying out new

21:06.273 --> 21:08.896
drugs. In fact, the first

21:11.239 --> 21:19.891
doses of several commonly used drugs were first at 
Texas A&M. For example? Yeah. Well,

21:31.964 --> 21:36.651
Oh, you have to watch

21:31.964 --> 21:36.651
me. Phenothiazine, for example.

21:41.377 --> 21:44.942
We were the first to show that phenothiazine could 
be poisonous to horses.

21:50.891 --> 21:51.752
When about was that? Oh, that was the 1940s. 1950s,

21:55.257 --> 22:00.925
thiobenzol, which is a common wormer.

